moosefs: MooseFS is a Petabyte Open Source Network Distributed File System.
moosefs: It is easy to deploy and maintain, highly reliable, fault tolerant,
moosefs: highly performing, easily scalable and POSIX compliant.
moosefs:
moosefs: MooseFS spreads data over a number of commodity servers, which are
moosefs: visible to the user as one resource. For standard file operations
moosefs: MooseFS acts like an ordinary Unix-like file system.
